In December 2016, Time named Trump as its "Person of the Year",[939] but Trump took issue with the magazine for referring to him as the "President of the Divided States of America".[940] In the same month, he was named Financial Times Person of the Year[941] and was ranked by Forbes the second most powerful person in the world after Vladimir Putin.[942] As president, Trump received the Collar of The Order of Abdulaziz al Saud from Saudi Arabia in 2017.[943]
